-- Colombian Stocks: Pacific Rubiales Energy, Petrominerales
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-06-05T21:31:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/colombian-stocks-pacific-rubiales-energy-petrominerales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.2 percent to 14,014.05 while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  dropped 0.2 percent to 1,660.65.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates
Colombia’s largest oil field, gained 0.4 percent to 44,800
pesos. The company agreed to acquire PetroMagdalena Energy Corp.
for C$1.60 a share.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMGC)  , a Calgary-based  oil company 
that operates in the Andean region, rallied 2.3 percent to
23,280 pesos. The company agreed to buy the remaining 20 percent
working interest in three Peruvian blocks from Veraz Petroleum
Ltd. for $5 million, payable in common shares of Petrominerales,
according to a press statement yesterday. The buyer will
“consolidate its participation in the Peru blocks, giving it
greater flexibility in its decisions,” Bolsa y Renta analysts
including Juliana Aguilar said in an e-mailed report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in  New York  at 
